Subject: mha_bwd: make v3_api_check a pure, side-effect-free dry-run probe

The v3_api_check flag is meant to answer "would the v3 ASM backward run
for this config?" (return 1 = yes, -1 = no) WITHOUT launching any kernel
or touching the driver/filesystem. The fwd path (mha_fwd.cu) already
honors this; the bwd path did not.

Two fixes to csrc/cpp_itfs/mha_bwd.cu:

  1. mha_bwd(): when the asm path returns -1 the function falls through to
     the v2 CK backward. A probe on a v3-unsupported config would therefore
     allocate a workspace and run a full v2 backward, clobbering dq/dk/dv
     instead of reporting -1. Return -1 immediately under v3_api_check so
     the probe stays side-effect-free (mirrors the fwd path).

  2. fmha_v3_bwd(): the `if(a.v3_api_check) return 1;` sat after all three
     ASM modules were loaded (AiterAsmKernel construction + .co file loads).
     Move it up to the config-availability point (right after kernel-name
     resolution), matching the fwd path which returns before any module
     load.

diff --git a/csrc/cpp_itfs/mha_bwd.cu b/csrc/cpp_itfs/mha_bwd.cu
index a57df7c2d..a0bed81de 100644
--- a/csrc/cpp_itfs/mha_bwd.cu
+++ b/csrc/cpp_itfs/mha_bwd.cu
@@ -135,6 +135,9 @@ float mha_bwd(mha_bwd_args a, const ck_tile::stream_config& s)
     if(asm_ret != -1)
         return asm_ret;
 
+    if(a.v3_api_check)
+        return -1;
+
     if(a.is_group_mode && (a.seqstart_q_ptr == nullptr || a.seqstart_k_ptr == nullptr))
     {
         AITER_LOG_ERROR("mha_bwd: group mode requires seqstart_q_ptr and seqstart_k_ptr");
@@ -377,6 +380,9 @@ float fmha_v3_bwd(mha_bwd_args a, const ck_tile::stream_config& s)
         return -1;
     }
 
+    if(a.v3_api_check)
+        return 1;
+
     int ts_odo;
     int ts_kv;
     int ts_dq;
@@ -438,9 +444,6 @@ float fmha_v3_bwd(mha_bwd_args a, const ck_tile::stream_config& s)
         }
     }
 
-    if(a.v3_api_check)
-        return 1;
-
     fmha_bwd_odo_args odo_args;
 
     odo_args.ptr_o           = a.o_ptr;
